VII 	 How do you manage your personal information
During your use of ChinesePro, you can access, correct and delete your personal information, and exercise the right to change the scope of authorization and consent and cancel your account. Your comments will be handled in a timely manner.
one 	 Access your personal information
You have the right to access your personal information, except for exceptions provided by laws and regulations. If you want to exercise the data access right, please click the "my" icon after logging in to the ChinesePro website, ChinesePro and ChinesePro applet. If you cannot access your personal information by yourself, please contact customer service for access.
two 	 Delete your personal information
For the personal information in your uploaded scanning file, you can delete the uploaded scanning file by yourself through our product page. Under the following circumstances, you can make a request to delete personal information to us, except for anonymization or otherwise provided by laws and regulations:
（1） 	 We collect and use personal information in violation of laws and regulations or agreements with you;
（2） 	 If we share or transfer your personal information with a third party in violation of laws and regulations or your agreement, we will immediately stop sharing and transfer and notify the third party to delete it in time;
（4） 	 You no longer use our products or services, or you cancel your account, or we terminate our services and operations.
If we decide to respond to your deletion request, we will also notify the entities that obtain your personal information from us in accordance with the provisions of laws, regulations and standard documents, and require them to delete your personal information in time, unless otherwise provided by laws and regulations, or these entities have obtained your independent authorization.
When you delete information from our service, we may not delete the corresponding information in the backup system immediately, but we will delete it when the backup is updated.
three 	 Change the scope of your authorization and consent
You can contact us through mobile phone permission settings or the methods specified in this privacy policy to change the scope of consent or withdraw your authorization.
Please understand that ChinesePro may need to open some permissions and collect necessary personal information to realize some services. When you withdraw your consent, we will not be able to continue to provide you with the services corresponding to the withdrawal of your consent, but will not affect the personal information processing services previously carried out based on your authorization.
four 	 Cancellation of account
You can contact us to cancel your account in the way specified in this privacy policy. We will delete your account within 15 working days after verifying your identity.
Customer service email:
app20190304@qq.com
Your cancellation of the above account is irreversible. We will stop providing you with products or services, no longer collect your personal information, and delete the personal information related to your account or anonymize it according to your requirements, unless otherwise stipulated by laws and regulations or required by regulatory authorities.
five 	 Automatic decision result appeal
In some business functions, we may only make decisions based on non manual automatic decision-making mechanisms including information systems and algorithms. If these decisions significantly affect your legitimate rights and interests, you have the right to contact us through the methods specified in this privacy policy to ask us to explain or complain about the automatic decision-making results of the information system.
Customer service email:
app20190304@qq.com
six 	 In response to your above request
If you are unable to exercise your rights in the above way, you can contact us by using the contact information specified in this privacy policy. For security, you may need to provide a written request or otherwise prove your identity. We may ask you to verify your identity before processing your request.
In principle, we will not charge for your reasonable request, but we will charge a certain cost for repeated requests that exceed the reasonable limit. We may refuse requests that are unreasonably repeated, require too many technical means, pose risks to the legitimate rights and interests of others, or are very impractical.
If your request is rejected, we will inform you of the reasons for the rejection, and you can complain through the contact information specified in this privacy policy.
seven 	 Exceptions to response situations
We will not be able to respond to your request if:
（1） 	 Related to our performance of our obligations under laws and regulations;
（2） 	 Directly related to national security and national defense security;
（3） 	 Directly related to public safety, public health and major public interests;
（4） 	 Directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgment;
（6） 	 For the purpose of safeguarding the life, property and other major legitimate rights and interests of the personal information subject or other individuals, but it is difficult to obtain my consent;
（7） 	 Responding to the request of the personal information subject will cause serious damage to the legitimate rights and interests of the personal information subject or other individuals and organizations;
（8） 	 Involving trade secrets.
VIII 	 How do we handle personal information about minors
Our products or services are mainly for adults (i.e. over the age of 18). In the process of providing products or services, we presume that you have corresponding civil capacity. If you are a minor (i.e. under the age of 18, the same below), we require you to ask your parents or other guardians to carefully read this Privacy Policy and use our services or provide us with information with the consent of your parents or other guardians.
If you are the legal guardian of a minor, please pay attention to whether the minor under your custody uses our products or services after obtaining your authorization and consent. If you have any questions about the personal information of the minors under your custody, please contact us through the methods specified in this privacy policy.
IX 	 How is this Privacy Policy updated
Our privacy policy may change in due course. We will post any changes to this Privacy Policy on this page. For major changes, we will also provide more significant notice (we may explain the specific changes to the privacy policy through a pop-up window) and obtain your consent again.
Without your express consent, we will not reduce your rights under this privacy policy.
Major changes referred to in this privacy policy include but are not limited to: major changes in our service model; The main objects of personal information sharing, transfer or public disclosure have changed; Significant changes have taken place in your right to participate in personal information processing and the way in which you exercise it; The responsible department, contact information and complaint channels responsible for handling personal information security have changed; When the personal information security impact assessment report indicates that there is a high risk.
